  "prompt": "Which is the correct past tense of override, overrode or overrided?",
  "response": "The correct past tense of **\"override\"** is **\"overrode.\"** \n\n- **Present:** override\n- **Past:** overrode\n- **Past Participle:** overridden\n\n**Example:**\n- *Yesterday, the manager **overrode** the initial decision.*\n\nUsing **\"overrided\"** is **not** standard in English and is generally considered incorrect.\n\nIf you have any more questions about verb conjugations or English grammar, feel free to ask!",
